---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const lastUpdated = 'June 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Roadmap"
  description="What we're building next for the Distilled CS framework, and why. We share our direction openly so CS teams can follow along and help shape what gets built."
>

  <div class="container roadmap-page">

    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      <h1 class="page-title">Distilled CS Roadmap</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">
        We believe in being open about what we're building and why. This page is where we share what's coming next, so the people using this framework can follow along, push back, and help shape what gets built.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="page-body">

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>What we're building</h2>
        <p>
          One of the principles we try to hold ourselves to is transparency: not just in the framework content, but in how we develop it. That means sharing direction early, being clear about what we're prioritising and why, and letting the needs of real CS teams drive what comes next.
        </p>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table class="roadmap-table">
            <colgroup>
              <col style="width: 60%">
              <col style="width: 20%">
              <col style="width: 20%">
            </colgroup>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Item</th>
                <th>Status</th>
                <th>Issue / Notes</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Re-assessment reminder: download a calendar invite to re-take the assessment in 90 days and keep the improvement loop moving</td>
                <td><span class="status status-planned">Planned</span></td>
                <td>—</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Site-wide search: find any metric, playbook, principle, or glossary term from a single search box</td>
                <td><span class="status status-planned">Planned</span></td>
                <td>—</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Resume an in-progress assessment: pick up where you left off instead of starting the questionnaire over</td>
                <td><span class="status status-planned">Planned</span></td>
                <td>—</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Gap-to-next-stage view: a visual map of the capability gaps between your current stage and the next, and the playbooks that close them</td>
                <td><span class="status status-exploring">Exploring</span></td>
                <td>Concept stage</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Anonymous CS score submission: optionally share your maturity score, industry, and company type to contribute to aggregate industry benchmark data</td>
                <td><span class="status status-planned">Planned</span></td>
                <td>—</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>What we've shipped</h2>
        <p>
          Items that have moved from the plan into the live framework. We keep them here so the history of the framework stays visible.
        </p>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table class="roadmap-table">
            <colgroup>
              <col style="width: 60%">
              <col style="width: 20%">
              <col style="width: 20%">
            </colgroup>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Item</th>
                <th>Status</th>
                <th>Notes</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>CS Metrics Map: show metric priority across all maturity stages in one view</td>
                <td><span class="status status-done">Shipped</span></td>
                <td>
                  <a href="https://github.com/saneeshnp/distilled-cs/commit/3ce50bb77e6495a5fa175e1d1b956cd44b6125be" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">V1</a>,
                  <a href="https://github.com/saneeshnp/distilled-cs/commit/d434ccc0f0c9beb594f617a6ae62d84290d65484" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">V2</a>,
                  <a href="https://github.com/saneeshnp/distilled-cs/commit/55c1715c48b25f85002a5720de8c7a54de6408d4" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">V3</a>
                </td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>How we decide what to build</h2>
        <p>
          Every addition to Distilled CS starts with the same question: does this help a CS team do their job better? Not more comprehensively, not more impressively, but more usefully. We weigh that against the stage the team is at and the constraints they're actually working under.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you have something specific you'd like to see, or want to tell us what's missing from the framework, the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> is the right place.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .roadmap-page {
    padding-block: 3rem 5rem;
    max-width: 56rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-accent-subtle);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 0 0.375rem 0.375rem 0;
  }

  .page-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2.5rem;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .content-section p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .content-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .table-wrapper {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0.625rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
  }

  .roadmap-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  .roadmap-table thead tr {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 8%, var(--color-surface));
  }

  .roadmap-table th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border-bottom: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 20%, transparent);
  }

  .roadmap-table td {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
    vertical-align: middle;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .roadmap-table tbody tr {
    transition: background 0.15s ease;
  }

  .roadmap-table tbody tr:hover {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 4%, transparent);
  }

  .roadmap-table tbody tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .roadmap-table td:first-child {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .roadmap-table a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .status {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.625rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .status-planned {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 12%, transparent);
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .status-in-progress {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #F57C00 15%, transparent);
    color: #F57C00;
  }

  .status-exploring {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-text-muted) 15%, transparent);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .status-done {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #388E3C 15%, transparent);
    color: #388E3C;
  }
</style>
